answers.body_markdown:
[`channel.members`][1] returns a list of all members that can see the channel. 

If you use the freeze command, you take away all members&#39; permissions (apart from the bot) to read messages and message history from the channel. In other words, they can no longer see the channel.

Because of this, when running the melt command, `channel.members` will not return any members as no member can see the channel.

Replacing this with [`guild.members`][2] will always return all members of the server, regardless of whether they can see the channels or not.

    @bot.command(name=&quot;freeze&quot;)
    async def zamroz(ctx):
        try:
            if ctx.message.author.guild_permissions.value == 2146959359:
                for channel in ctx.guild.text_channels:
                    for member in ctx.guild.members:
                        if member.bot == False:
                            await channel.set_permissions(member, read_messages=False, read_message_history=False)
            else:
                await ctx.send(&quot;Lack of permissions&quot;)
                await ctx.channel.last_message.delete(delay=2)
        except:
            pass
    
    @bot.command(name=&quot;melt&quot;)
    async def odmroz(ctx):
        try:
            if ctx.message.author.guild_permissions.value == 2146959359:
                for channel in ctx.guild.text_channels:
                    for member in ctx.guild.members:
                        if member.bot == False:
                            await channel.set_permissions(member, overwrite=None)
            else:
                await ctx.send(&quot;Lack of permissions&quot;)
                await ctx.channel.last_message.delete(delay=2)
        except:
            pass


  [1]: https://discordpy.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api.html#discord.TextChannel.members
  [2]: https://discordpy.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api.html#discord.Guild.members

